{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12dd2f98-660c-45f3-b136-3da583a924af","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's the summary:\n\n### 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\nMSTest v4 changed the **default test-ID generation strategy**. Azure DevOps keys history on test ID, so every test looks new. To restore history, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n```\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level context** — it no longer carries a test name because the method runs once per class, not per test. Accessing `TestName` now throws.\n\nYour `SetupTests.cs` hits this directly on line 13. Fix: guard or remove that access.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_016g5Livsde4VuqACSdLuHFW","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d2cbddffaefc4570a36a7c17343b132c/SetupTests.cs","old_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        var testName = context.TestName;\n        // Log setup for specific test\n    }","new_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // In MSTest v4 the ClassInitialize context is class-scoped;\n        // TestName is only available inside [TestInitialize] or [TestMethod].\n        var className = context.FullyQualifiedTestClassName;\n        // Log class-level setup\n    }"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d2cbddffaefc4570a36a7c17343b132c/SetupTests.cs."}],"interactionId":"4aa9441f-9a06-4ae1-9704-4a2493049c6e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has upgraded to MSTest v4 and is encountering two specific issues. Let me address both, plus provide additional watch-outs.\n\n1. **Test IDs changed → lost history in Azure DevOps**: MSTest v4 changed the default test ID generation strategy. In v3, the fully qualified test name was used. In v4, the default test ID is now based on a stable, deterministic hash. This means Azure DevOps sees them as new tests. The fix is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>` to `DisplayName` or the legacy value, or use the `[TestId]` attribute.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. \n\n2. **TestContext.TestName in [ClassInitialize]**: In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a \"class-level\" context that doesn't have test-specific information. `TestName` is no longer available in that context and throws. This makes sense because `[ClassInitialize]` runs once for the class, not per test.\n\n3. Other things to watch out for in MSTest v4: The `[TestClass]` attribute is now required, `TestContext` properties must be non-nullable or use the `required` modifier, `DeploymentItem` behavior has changed, parallelism defaults may differ, `DataRow` and `DynamicData` attributes work differently, `Assert.Inconclusive` behaves differently, and several deprecated APIs have been removed. Let me work through both issues and provide a concrete fix.","outputTokens":874,"requestId":"67C3:1F16:1B4A5EA:1ECB522:69FD5452"},"id":"1e9a7715-951e-44c7-95e3-d9ba0f7dabe7","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:11:32.351Z","parentId":"3ad01142-3738-4298-9844-aaa67b0c558e"}
{"type":"tool.execution_start","data":{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_016g5Livsde4VuqACSdLuHFW","toolName":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d2cbddffaefc4570a36a7c17343b132c/SetupTests.cs","old_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        var testName = context.TestName;\n        // Log setup for specific test\n    }","new_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // In MSTest v4 the ClassInitialize context is class-scoped;\n        // TestName is only available inside [TestInitialize] or [TestMethod].\n        var className = context.FullyQualifiedTestClassName;\n        // Log class-level setup\n    }"}},"id":"1215c354-2d33-43d7-87c0-3e2f77bbaeaf","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:11:32.352Z","parentId":"1e9a7715-951e-44c7-95e3-d9ba0f7dabe7"}
