{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1087854c-6d0e-40c2-956d-7c75bd2fa6d0","content":"### 3. Other v4 watch-outs\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Parallelism** | Class-level parallelism is now the default; tests that relied on sequential execution may race. Opt out with `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]` or disable entirely. |\n| **`TestContext` property** | Should now be `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; } = default!;` or marked `required` — nullable warnings are stricter. |\n| **`Assert.Inconclusive`** | No longer caught by `ExpectedException`; it's treated as a distinct outcome. |\n| **Timeout behavior** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` via `TestContext.CancellationTokenSource` instead of thread-abort; long-running tests need to check the token. |\n| **`[DeploymentItem]`** | Paths are resolved differently; verify if you copy test data files. |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4aa9441f-9a06-4ae1-9704-4a2493049c6e","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"67C3:1F16:1B4F10D:1ED0976:69FD5464"},"id":"ad858c69-e7ca-4be2-ae11-4576f4ccf415","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:11:40.718Z","parentId":"5472f429-bed0-4ed3-81c4-4812435cd4d0"}
